                    <note>
                        <ab type="description">ʾAmḥarā is the name of an historical area in central
                                <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName>. This place-name
                            does not appear in the sources of the Aksumite period and its earlierst
                            preserved mention can be found in a manuscript of the
                            <!--"Golden Gospel"--> of <placeName ref="">Dabra Libānos</placeName>
                            dating to <date when="1322">1322</date>. These mentions became numerous
                            in Ethiopic medieval sources and increased over time. The importance of
                            this area seems to have increased after the fall of the <persName ref=""
                                >Zagʷe</persName> dinasty and the re-establishment of the Solomonic
                            dinasty in the <date notBefore="1250" notAfter="1300">late 13th
                                century</date>. </ab>
                    </note>
